## Origin

Distilled from recurring manual-reviewer feedback patterns:

- §11 (Doc-06 crash-safety) — surfaced repeatedly when a runtime flake leaves `/logs/verifier/reward.txt` unwritten and the platform synthesises a "verifier did not run" row.
- §12 (difficulty alignment) — flagged across multiple reviews where the `-medium` / `-hard` directory suffix, `task.toml difficulty` field, test-suite docstring, and time-estimate fields disagreed in pairs or triples.
- §13 (task.toml field completeness) — observed when a missing `[environment].workdir` field combined with a `difficulty` mismatch produced two independent rejection signals in one review pass. The lesson generalises: every field the validator parses needs to be present AND consistent with the other four artifacts that mirror it.
